EXPERIMENT 2: CALCULATOR APP USING FLUTTER – VIVA QUESTIONS & ANSWERS

1. What is Dart?
   Dart is an object-oriented programming language developed by Google used for building Flutter applications.

2. Why Flutter uses Dart?
   Because Dart compiles to native code, provides high performance, and supports Hot Reload. 

3. What is a Widget?
   A widget is a reusable UI component used to build the interface of a Flutter application.

4. What is StatelessWidget?
   A widget whose UI does not change during runtime.

5. What is StatefulWidget?
   A widget whose UI can change dynamically using state and setState().

6. What is setState()?
   setState() updates the UI when data changes.

7. What is the role of build() method?
   build() defines how the UI looks.

8. What is Scaffold?
   Scaffold provides the basic app structure like AppBar and body.

9. What is Column widget?
   Column arranges widgets vertically.

10. What is Row widget?
    Row arranges widgets horizontally.

11. What is Expanded widget?
    Expanded is used to give equal space to widgets.

12. What is the function of ElevatedButton?
    It creates clickable buttons in Flutter.

13. What is the purpose of display variable?
    It stores and shows the calculator output.

14. What happens when '=' is pressed?
    The calculation is performed and result is displayed.

15. What is operator variable used for?
    It stores the selected arithmetic operation.

16. What is num1 and num2?
    They store input numbers for calculation.

17. What is Hot Reload?
    It updates UI instantly without restarting the app.

18. What is the output of this experiment?
    A working calculator app performing basic operations.

19. Why StatefulWidget is used here?
    Because the UI changes based on user input.

20. What platforms Flutter supports?
    Android, iOS, Web, Windows, macOS, Linux.

END OF VIVA
